Hi there,

You can do it as it's mentioned in #2213 .

```js
const search = instantsearch({
  indexName: 'instant_search',
  searchClient,
  searchFunction: helper => {
    helper.setQueryParameter('hitsPerPage', 5).search();
  },
});
```

Thanks for answering ! It's very helpful.

> use connectConfigure instead of configure and call its refine function when it needs to change

@Haroenv there is a best practice to detect if the user has filtered with the Menu widget in my custom configure function ?

The [Algolia demo](https://www.algolia.com/search/) is exactly what I want.

By default, **Website** has a hitsPerPage: 6.

When I click on **Website** in the **Menu** (before the searchbox), the hitsPerPage of **Website** changes to 16.

When I reclick on the **Website** in the **Menu**, the hitsPerPage of **Website** returns to 6.
_______________________
In my code, I try to refine the hitsPerPage based on the `hierarchicalFacetsRefinements` but I get an infinite loop.

```javascript
const renderConfigure = (renderOptions, isFirstRender) => {
  const { refine, instantSearchInstance } = renderOptions

  if (instantSearchInstance.helper) {
    const hierarchicalFacetsRefinements = instantSearchInstance.helper.state.hierarchicalFacetsRefinements['post_type']

    if (hierarchicalFacetsRefinements.length > 0) {
      refine({ hitsPerPage: 16 })
    } else {
      refine({ hitsPerPage: 6 })
    }
  }
}
```

I found a way but it's very dirty 😄 In my `renderConfigure` function I check if `hierarchicalFacetsRefinements` is not empty and the value of the attribute of the container defined in the `customConfigure` options, then I refine my hitsPerPage.

